text: Pribumia is a genus of southeastern Asian cellar spiders first described by B. A. Huber, J. Eberle & D. Dimitrov in 2018. ==Species== it contains six species: *Pribumia atrigularis (Simon, 1901) — Malaysia, Singapore, Indonesia *Pribumia bohorok (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Sumatra) *Pribumia diopsis (Simon, 1901) — Thailand *Pribumia hurau (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Sumatra) *Pribumia minang (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Sumatra) *Pribumia singalang (Huber, 2011) — Indonesia (Sumatra) ==References== ==External links== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Pholcidae
title: Pribumia
